Vol / Page:  4/300
Edition:
Quote:  (Report on Grasses) <i>Trisetum antarcticum</i>. Oat-grass. - A local grass, widely distributed; found from sea-level to 1,500 feet in dry soil; flowers October to January; useful in spring and summer; is affected by drought; a valuable grass.
Notes:

